<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Pzar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I just installed windows 2000 on my computer and now I am able to play EQ for a measly 10 secs or so before it freezes up.<P>Installed new drivers for graphics and sound.<BR>Put nosound.txt in EQ dir.<P>But still no EQ for me.<P>Anyone know how to fix this. PLEASE  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>Pzar.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Katandon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Update your DirectX to latest version, get different drivers for your Video (try older ones), or get a different card.  Verant is not going to give you any support, so you're just gonna have to fight with it.<P>------------------<BR>Katandon Scarletrose<BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR>Quellious</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aladain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Pzar:<BR><B>I just installed windows 2000 on my computer and now I am able to play EQ for a measly 10 secs or so before it freezes up.<P>Installed new drivers for graphics and sound.<BR>Put nosound.txt in EQ dir.<P>But still no EQ for me.<P>Anyone know how to fix this. PLEASE   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>Pzar.</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I know this sounds silly, and dont do it if you dont feel comfortable with it.<P>In BIOS if you can set these, check these.  If you dont know how to do it or dont wanna risk it, don't do it.<P>(If AGP Video) AGP ap. grill size: 128 MB<BR>Slow your memory (Add waitstates - note this might affect overall performance)<BR>(If PCI Video) Force PCI_66 GAT Mode: Off<P>These have solved issues with Windows 2000 and EQ for me.  Hope it helps!<P>Aladain<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Pzar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">AGP size at 128.<P>No changes  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>HELP  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Pzar.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Brokk</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have been useing win2k to play EQ since it came out.  The only tricky thing is makeing sure your hardware has very good driver support for win2k.  I am using a Voodoo5 and a SbLive 5.1 Mp3+  Because 3DFX put out an awsome driver the video is great but the sound sux because Creative labs is slacking and don't have any new liveware for the 5.1 versoion of the SBlive that supports win2k.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gabriel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I had problems when I first started playing EQ and I'm using Win2000. I'd log in and at the character screen or once in the game, within ten minutes I'd completly freeze.<P>I fixed this by disabling my sound card in the hardware manager (Win2000 uses APCI which shares IRQs - check to see if your Sound and Video care share the same IRQ).<P>A couple weeks ago, they released the Win2000 patches which seemed to work. I updated my sound card with the latest drivers, lowered the performance on it, and changed the default device to a Win device.<P>I've had no problems since then.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Malore</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Microsoft has released atleast one service pack and a few other patches that address issues such as these.  Just run Windows Update and you should be good.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Boradaf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The biggest thing I have seen with Win2k and hardware is, if you use the standard settings during install, IRQ 11 will be shared by your audio card, video card, USB ports, and about half a dozen other pieces of hardware.<P>To correct this, I went into BIOS and set the option of "PnP aware OS" (Plug and Play aware Operating System) to "NO".<P>Then in the hardware manager find the item that says "Computer".  It will say it is a system that uses a 4 letter acronym that escapes me right now, but I think it starts with an "A".  Update the driver for that and tell it to show you all the options for that device.  Select "Standard PC", and allow it to find the drivers for that, it may ask for the disk.<P>Anyway, after it does that, you will have to re-install all your hardware drivers, sound, video, lan card/modem, etc.<P>When you go back and check the IRQs, your video and sound card will be on their own IRQ and not shared.<P>I had to go through all this when I upgraded my CPU and sound card.  I was having a horrible time staying in the game with it locking up, crashing to the desktop, or other nasty things you don't want to happen when you are staring at mobs in Dreadlands.<P>I wish you good luck getting things sorted out and all.  I hope this wasn't too vague or hard to understand.  If any part of this is over your head, find a good friend that is a techie and get him to help you out.<P>Best,<BR>Boradaf Starforge<BR>46 Cleric - The Rathe</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Xthor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My W2K install would freeze for 10 seconds, then play for 20, then freeze for 10 again.  I updated to directx 8.whatever, and now it works fine.<P>Hope you get it worked out before you go too far into withdrawl!<P>=)<P>Xthor Mednheal<BR>Cleric of 40 Seasons<BR>Solace Keep<BR>Druzzil Ro<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Pzar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Worked it out by removing Win2k and going back to Win ME.<BR>Now everything is dandy again  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Pzar.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rennhelm</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmm, obviously user experiance highly varies.  I have 2 systems I can play EQ with here, and both use Win2000, and while one of them is a bit slow, they are both rock-solid for many hours of raiding / exp grinding fun.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Katandon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Keep in mind Verant did not develop, nor did they test EQ on Win2k.  I find it amazing that it works at all, at least for some people.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/tongue.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Katandon Scarletrose<BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR>Quellious</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aladain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Boradaf:<BR><B>The biggest thing I have seen with Win2k and hardware is, if you use the standard settings during install, IRQ 11 will be shared by your audio card, video card, USB ports, and about half a dozen other pieces of hardware.<P>To correct this, I went into BIOS and set the option of "PnP aware OS" (Plug and Play aware Operating System) to "NO".</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Very good suggestion.<P>I would also mention that on SOME PCs (The Asus K7M MB is like this) - having ACPI on, even if PnP is off, will cause Win 2000 to do this as well.  If you have the option to turn ACPI off AND PnP OS Off, thats cool.  PnP OS On on some machines doesnt mess this up, but most it does.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alle</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I know it doesn't help but I have 2 different systems running W2K and both of them work fine.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
